review_text: About 25.5 miles from West Hartford to this (end of the trail). Good round-trip bike riding route. Provided awesome scenery while resting. Sadly, no public restroom is available.
The esplanade is aa great place to sip a coffee, have a snack, watch the water or just enjoy nature.  The old railroad bridge was refurbished for use as a trail across the Westfield River.
Smooth cool ride, wish it was stretched out more for longer riding and had fountain on the bikeway side as well. Amazing fun riding  both ways.
This mural is a fantastic work in progress primarily being painted by artists Sarah Kinne and Shannon Chiba. -- A new entry to the espanade will be from the bridge  and new trail from downtown area.
The Esplanade is a nice, pleasant place by the Westfield River with nice views, lots of benches, trash bins, lights, and a of the section bike trail.
The bridge is beautiful over the river and the place is amazing
It's very relaxing, to sit and watch the Westfield River.
It's just a great quiet place to sit and think

Beautiful River, I went kayaking down it for 3 hours last summer and it was such a wonderful experience, the water is so clear you can see right to the bottom in most places! i had hardly seen any trash floating in the water, (of course there were a few pieces!) gone swimming in this river a few times and was fine after. alot of beautiful scenery and i hope to continue the journey this summer!
I've never considered snorkeling in the river, but another reviewer suggested that it is indeed, a thing. It is a wonderful river to visit. Industry has managed to not affect it's natural beauty.

Love the Westfield River! The Westfield Wildwater races in April are a great way to challenge yourself at any level, with a river that stays interesting and challenging the whole way through. You can also access the calmer side of the river at the bridges in Westfield and cruise to Robinson State Park when water is high enough... or all the way to it's outlet into the Connecticut River just South of Springfield.
Clean river great for swimming snorkeling and kayaking. Many deep holes and large parts of its upper watershed vey undeveloped.
Beautiful, quaint, clean and great fishing.
I would love to find the way but it brings you to a wrong place. I was looking for an hour and didnt find it.
Nice
Quiet place

A great place for children to spend time. A small space, but enough to find activities for the child. Clean toilets, order in the play areas. The staff frequently walked around and tidied up the toys. The only downside is the floors, there is some trash... not much... a vacuum cleaner would solve the problem. And of course, it would be better if being on the premises was without shoes. Some children don't walk, they crawl, and it's not pleasant when everyone walks in shoes, especially in the rain. If being in socks only was allowed, the floors would be much cleaner.

I got there early on the weekend and myself and my 2 year old were the only ones there for about a hour till a birthday party rolled in, I will definitely be back, my son loved it But I would probably go on a weekday instead of weekend. It maybe small but there's tons for your little ones! And it's affordable too!

Cute place for toddlers! A lot of activities to keep them exploring. We bought a pass as something to do on rainy or super hot/cold days! My girls love the rocket ship and the kitchen area! Staff is friendly! It can get busy on vacations and weekends but still plenty of room to play!

Nice Children's Museum. Great place to go if you're local. They have an excellent deal on Thursdays.
It's got fun activities for toddlers up to kindergarten. They have a rocket ship for kids to play in, a slide, a milking cow, a play campsite, bank, kitchen, dentist, a broadcasting booth, Dino dig site,  an art room with activities, and live reptiles to look at.

Small children's museum that is good for toddlers and young children. The staff was kind and available for help as needed. The facility needs some TLC, updating and repairs as the equipment, exhibits and bathrooms are pretty worn down and dirty. The toilet seat in the stall I used in the women's bathroom almost came off as I sat down, the family bathroom has a super small changing table which was disgustingly dirty. They ask that you put diapers in bags before disposing but no bags are provided and the garbage bin  itself was in the middle of the bathroom without a bag. I got in with discounted tickets and my 1 year old enjoyed herself- my 8 month old didn't have too much to do. I would've enjoyed it less if I had to pay full price for the 4 tickets I needed as I went with 3 adults and a child. It was okay. Probably won't be returning or recommending.

I love it here compared to other places. Nice open area that is both educational and interactive. I find it easy to go here just to have some play time with my 2 year old and 10 month old. I will say it's hard to get them to want to leave but you spend an hour or 2 here and the kids will go straight to sleep. I wish there were more places like this in the area. This place should be a staple for other local towns who don't have a lot to do for young families

We love this museum but it is so dirty. It's worse because all the carpets have patterns so it hides the dirt, but when you look closely it's covered with junk. It needs to be vacuumed daily but I'm not sure if it is because even if you arrive at 9am, the floor is covered in snacks, wrapper, pieces from the fossil exhibit, and so much dirt and dust. Just buy more vacuums and clean it more. The staff doesn't interact with visitors at all but they are not cleaning, so just change that and require a little more cleaning! Also, the toddler toys are lacking. They need to be replaced and refreshed much more often. Again, it's a great museum but clean it more!

Fun but small place. Many different area can let kids play: camping, building house, sliding, archaeological open kitchen, and shopping. They also have many activities and small animals can see. Ticket is $8/person.

I wish I had more photos of the park, but Stanley is so gorgeous. Took my senior pictures and had a picnic here -- nearly every spot is scenic! Clear paths for walking in the woods are nice. Had a field trip in junior high to the playground area. Tennis courts were great, too. Overall a well kept and enjoyed place by all!
Wonderful playground. Feeding the geese, ducks, and fish was nice. When the roses bloom soon we will be going again to see them. Love this place since I was a child.

Lovely place. However as a dog walkimg enthusiast it can be incredibly annoying to see dog droppings everywhere on the path.

Clean up after your dog or at least use a stick to flick that stuff off the trail! Making us look bad out there peope

All-time favorite park. We have been going here since the 80s. Peaceful place to walk and look at the luscious gardens of green manicured grass and beautiful plants. The buildings and statues are well maintained. Enjoy the walk around the pond and sitting watching the wildlife and fish in the pond, and let's not forget the black squirrels. A must go to enjoy this beautiful park.

Great park!! Room for all kinds of activities. They have an amazing playground, big fields, a huge covered sandbox, tennis, handball, picnic area with grills and it's so big!  There's bathrooms that are clean. The park itself is clean and kept up with very well. I know we'll be going back.

This is one of the most beautiful, well laid out, and well-kept parks I have ever seen. Duck pond/coi pond area is very peaceful and serene, lots of open field for soccer, lacrosse, Frisbee, etc. Awesome playground area with a dynamic range of swings, slides, sand boxes, climbing courses. Great family picnic area. There is plenty of parking and seating. You can spend hours there!

One of the best parks around, with tons to do.
There's an excellent playground with equipment, swings, slides, sandbox and seesaws.
There's nature trails and plenty of picnic tables.
There's beautiful trees, plants, and fields.
Rose garden, duck pond, tea house.
The list goes on, it's just a nice place to be outside enjoying nature.
There are very nice pavilions available for rental too.

Be aware there is NO SMOKING anywhere at the park, you can be subject to a fine.
There is also no picnicking or dogs allowed in the rose garden.
Professional photographers need to buy a pass.

Don't feed the ducks/geese/fish bread, only seed and food from the feeder machines (take quarters). Don't try to touch the birds or let your kids touch them. They will bite and it's a preserve specifically for them, so just admire them.

Stanley Park is beautiful. I thoroughly enjoyed walking through the rose garden and looking at all the plants. The ponds are wonderful (koi, ducks & geese, frogs & turtles). There are benches throughout to sit and enjoy your surroundings or rest. The bathrooms were clean.
Great scenic view good place to go fishing in the summer
It's a river I'm not sure what else to say about it

From the moment I set the bike on the paved railway, I knew I was in for a treat. The smoothness of the path, the gentle hum of the wheels on the paved path, and the scenic views that unfolded with each mile were nothing short of spectacular.
The attention to detail on this railway is commendable. The path is meticulously maintained, ensuring a safe and comfortable ride for all.  What truly sets this railway apart is its integration with the surrounding landscape. Riding along, you're treated to a tapestry of nature's finest work, from lush greenery to panoramic vistas. It's the perfect blend of modern convenience and natural beauty, will need to take some photos next time.
I walk this railtrail several times a week. Bikers are usually polite and let a pediatrician know that they are approaching. It's a great trail to walk your dog and is wheelchair friendly

Beautiful bike trail. The trail is well kept. I've never seen any brush or branches in the way, it's always kept clear. The views are amazing having bridges run over brooks and small bodies of water. There are really cool mural tunnels that you pass under every once a while. There's always wildlife to see such as birds and squirrels. There are bear sittings every once and a while but I've personally never came across one lucky. Would recommend this trail to anyone looks for a nice place to pass some time and get some exercise,
This is the "local name" for the New Haven/Northampton Canal trail bike path. It's as nice as the rest of the path.

The Greenway is an amazing asset in our city that connects to southwick and through Connecticut. Its beautifully scenic, well maintained and a great trail to ride, run or walk. I'm very excited for the final phase of construction where the trail will extend through downtown and end at the twin bridges.
It's very clean and the pavement is fairly new. I enjoyed my ride. Only wish there were  mileage markers like on the Northampton trail. Thank you guys

I left my house in Easthampton and biked all the way to Drakes Hill Bridge of Flowers in Simsbury. It was an excellent ride, this is a beautiful expanse of bike trail. I wish the bike trail connected Southampton and the rest of Westfield. It was great to get on the bike trail again, having biked through Westfield.
I've ridden this trail in its entirety many times, always exhilarating and a bit of a challenge! It's also a great place to learn to ride and test out your bike!

The place was filthy and at least 1/3 of the games were out of order. The kids who worked there were nice but I didn't see one adult on the premises. The kitchen was closed on a Saturday night so we couldn't even get our granddaughter a snack which was actually a blessing considering how dirty everything was. As a preschool teacher in the area, I had considered Big Adventures as a field trip location until our visit. I will never go back and would not recommend it.

I was not at all happy with this visit.... we decided to go because the website made it look amazing exciting and fun.... nothing on the websites tells anyone that "its under some kind of construction(work)". I would say that's some pretty false advertisement.  Most of the arcade games didn't work or didn't give tickets or would just eat your tokens... Its fully understaffed, so in turn when there are any problems with the games not working the staff are too busy to even help. This place should not be open right now, or there should be an actually "mechanic" on staff to fix things. The place wasn't too bad except for the ball pits with crushed balls.... and the slides that "don't slide"
Plus the food, yeah its not badly priced but you definitely get what you play for, I got popcorn... most of the box was popcorn kernels and the popcorn was cold.
So disappointing!!!!

3/4 of the games are broken, either out of order or eat your money or don't give tickets. Food is over priced and not very good. Most of the play are is in okay condition with a lot of tears repaired with duct tape. The toddler area is very small and over run with older kids. No balls in the "ball pit" and the bounce house wasn't up and running. As for cleanliness.... This one won't win any awards. Food everywhere, especially in the food area. Kids everywhere banging on machines, no wonder they don't work. The smell in there was horrible. Needlessly said we didn't stay very long and won't be returning.

Umm where to begin? Pictures on the website make it look so fun, clean, and makes it look like there's a lot to do. Well, 90% of the games are broken and had signs that have been on it for at least a year saying " sorry not feeling well".  The tubes, ball pits, and climbing equipment are FILTHY and half of it is held together by zip ties and electrical tape. Doesn't look safe at all. Half the machines ate your money and you cannot get it back. The few games that actually do work Dont have tickets in them. So if you win, u lose your tickets anyways. The food...disgusting! I was wondering why there was throw up in 2 out of the 3 toilets in the girls room. I'm guessing that was why. The dining area to sit and eat was also filthy. Half the tables had trays of food that looked like it had been there a few days to a week. I'm not one to EVER write a review, but this place is a complete garbage dump. The website is defiantly deceiving. I will never ever bring my kids there again. I wouldn't even if someone paid me to bring them there. Never. This place needs the board of health and other agencies to come shut it down.

This place is disgusting and filthy.  In addition the employees are rude and like to harass the children.  While I was there, I witnessed an employee bullying a little girl (maybe 6).  When the mother yelled at the employee for speaking to her daughter that way, the employee tried to hit the mother.  If I was that mother, they would have taken that employee out on a stretcher.  Also, the balls were all wet with some type of liquid and I tried to let a staff member know, but they could have cared less.  Instead, she gave me a bad attitude and stormed off.  About 97% of the games in the arcade were out of order and the lighting leaves alot to be desired. If you want to be over-charged, let your children play in filth and be bullied, than this is the place for you.  Otherwise, parents DO NOT TAKE YOUR CHILDREN HERE!

Half the games are always broken and it's a haven for germs. I understand kids spread germs don't get me wrong, however this stuff hasn't been clean in I would say, ever. I climbed through the tunnels and there was two inch thick dust, lost socks, juice boxes and other items lodged in crevices and on top of the plays capes.

This place is terrible. The customer service is bad.half the games dont work bathroom door dont have a lock or one doesnt flush. Waited forever for our food. I cant wait for billy beez in holyoke mall to open
local DDR machine???? with an eatery, water fountain and nearby bathrooms????? literally all I could ask for, plus the playscape & games are fun for kids. great place!

This place opens at 10:30 am and the parking space is big and close to the area, so its not so much walking to do.
The lake is big and nice, a lot of goose pup, but still nice.
It has  big gazebos and the grills are all around the place, it has picnic tables and a lot of green area with a lot of trees around  for shade.
The water is not too clean but still nice.

Beautiful pond. Plenty of picnic tables. Nice big beach and swimming area. Walking and fishing is great here. Seperate boat ramp and parking. Motorized boats allowed so be aware if kayaking or canoeing. All around a nice park to go to.

Our favorite place to hang out or go for walks with a dog. Sometimes kayaking. We swim there too although you have to check first when it is safe or not safe to do so. They will post it.
One dislike  - some people on jetSki's swim very aggressively sometimes and too close to the ages of the pond so when you are swimming near shore in a wild part of the pond closer to the fishing area - we are worried that they will run us over :(

Nestled in Westfield is a beautiful small lake surrounded by homes, hilly terrain  and woodlands.  It has several nice sized beaches some with shelters, picnic areas & fire boxes for grilling to entertain families on those hot summer days.  There is boating, canoeing, paddle boats, water skiing, fishing, hiking and lots of other ways to enjoy yourself.  It makes for a picturesque setting with many of subjects just poising for you to take a picture.  Walk the streets with the shore homes you'll be surprised.  There is a Fighter Reserve Base near by and youigjt get a to see F18's taking off vertically, fly around usually in pairs and close ups as they land.  It is quite a sight.  Enjoy, we certainly did and will again.

The place is good if you want to stay by the water and fry meat, spend time with family and friends.  There are many tables, toilet.  There is a swimming area and parking.  But I don't like opening hours.  Late to open and close early.  For the summer period, this watch is not successful.  And the rest I like this lake and its arrangement.
would give more stars if I could! Beautiful place to go out on the kayak or go fishing. friendly staff that roam around and nice beach to swim in. 12/10!

Found the water a bit murky and a lit of lilly pads into the swimming area. I believe they did a treatment day before, and it made the lilly pads rise to the surface. Ice cream trucks came twice while i was there. Shade and pavilions avail. No balls allowed in water. Doesn't get very deep in the buoy area, but still ok for swimming. Life guards were friendly and attentive. Water was pretty warm/ nice

My favorite place to be not just during the summer, but year round. I love the peace and tranquility and enjoy the wild life. My grandkids love being pulled on the tube with the boat. Water skiing and of course swimming and fishing . In the winter it's ice fishing and skating.

This place is super fun for all ages. My 9 and 11 years old boys had a blast playing in all the different areas... so many trampolines, basketball, soccer, dodge ball, obstacle course, ball pit slides, rock claiming, arcade area, lego blocks, toddler area, party rooms area ect. Pricing per hour was very reasonable and they have drinks and snacks machines. There were a lot of people, but the place is so big it didn't feel crowded at all. The place was very clean, including the bathrooms. There was seating for the adults in the different areas, as well as massage chairs. The staff was knowledgeable and pleasant. The glow in the dark was the cherry on top. I recommend Funz 100%.

We recently took our grandchildren to Funz trampoline park on a school day off, and it was an absolute blast! The facility is impressively large and well-monitored, ensuring a safe and controlled environment for all the fun. Beyond just trampolines, there are exciting "ninja warrior" style courses, basketball and soccer courts, providing endless entertainment options.

While the arcade area was a bit pricey and seemed somewhat unmaintained, it didn't detract from the overall fantastic experience. However, I do hope they consider adding a food court or a place to purchase snacks and drinks for added convenience.

Overall, Funz trampoline park offers a thrilling and enjoyable day out for the whole family, and I highly recommend it for anyone looking for an active and exciting adventure!

We visited on a Thursday evening and there were other guests, a couple of parties, but not too crowded. The employees were friendly, helpful, and attentive. The facility was so clean compared to other places like this that we've been. I was especially impressed with the cleanliness of the restrooms. A few small sections were roped off for repair but all of the installations were open, safe, and I'm good condition. Our family really enjoyed ourselves! We have a toddler and a 2nd grader and there was so much for each of them to do, along with obstacles that they can look forward to when they are older.

My x daughter in law had my grandson's birthday there. Quite pricey for 1 hour of bouncing, but, it was a nice place. I'd take a couple grandkids back. All of them would cost me a million dollars. Not to mention everything is extra. Games, that u must play of course, and soda n snack machines. I think they provided the room, and party bags. She supplied the rest. Pizza, drinks and snacks from home.

It is cool . So much fun for the kids . You can pay for an hour , or more , as long as  you want . No chewing gum allowed.
Restrooms are very clean . You have to sign a waiver before start the fun.

Very rude kids working here the bathrooms do not get cleaned they are so gross.My son came out where they have the ball pit and there is only concrete there he busted his whole face there should be something on the floor there instead it's under the tables which I don't get.They claim they clean and wipe down everything no they do not the ball pit was dusty and filthy I found all types of stuff hair ties,money,change, dirty used socks it was bad.the pizza sucks the drinks are over priced...I left due to all this and the unsanitary place and couldn't get a refund they were just rude. The toddler area and ball pit which is part of toddler area is always used by big kids throwing balls playing rough you can't even let your toddler have fun because they might get walked on or over the big kids are going up and down the slide the wrong way.

First time here good experience my son loved it but he spend most of his time at the dodgeball. Definitely loved when they turned the lights off and put rave lights on and music but the only thing that sucked was they didn't keep playing music they kept pausing it killing the vib

Great place for the kids to burn some energy for easy bedtime. They are always modifying and improving the course. My only critique is they need a new system for the arcade,the cards you buy don't work sometimes and it's really frustrating to call the hotline to fix the problem. But, if you are there for the jumping and the obstacle course, and the ball pit playground, it's pretty great!

This is our first year playing park n rec soccer and the kids had fun but it was extremely disorganized.  There were no coaches each week and the parents had to coach and parents are arguing it was a mess! This is week 3 and idk if we will be back next week.
Westfield parks are nice and maintained. They have a lot of different programs for kids.
Quick response when called for event info.
Friendly staff!

The kids had a blast learning and interacting with some awesome animals. If your looking to try something different for your little ones birthday events, i highly recommend the family jungle entertainment.
response_from_owner_text: Thankyou for the review. Happy everyone enjoyed all the family jungle animals.

review_text: Very educational and entertaining show for everyone. All of our guests had a blast with Family Jungle Entertainment. They loved learning about all the animals and meeting them all as well. Highly recommend!!
response_from_owner_text: We are happy to hear that  everyone enjoyed the show.. Thankyou for having us...

review_text: They put on a great show for my daughter birthday
response_from_owner_text: Thankyou happy everyone had fun with all the  animals.

review_text: Awesome  really nice entertainment for kids & adult really good prices
Kids had a great time with the animals
Amazing!!!
response_from_owner_text: Thankyou

review_text: Excelente show para toda la familia...muy educativo ...verdaderamente es un safari donde se disfrutar de una variedad de animales exotics.
response_from_owner_text: Muchisimas gracias.... Vendran muchas cosas nuevas para este VERANO 2022.
review_translated_text: Excellent show for the whole family...very educational...it is truly a safari where you can enjoy a variety of exotic animals.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you very much.... Many new things will come for this SUMMER 2022.

review_text: Excelente show....para toda la familia y muy educativo
review_translated_text: Excellent show...for the whole family and very educational

place_name: New England Trail at Robinson State Park
review_text: Alot of different trails. Beautiful little waterfall. I enjoy this park

place_name: New England Trail at Robinson State Park
review_text: Trails are nice but needs a lot of forestry management throughout. I saw a lot of high hazard areas for potential forest fires lots of dead hung up trees  suspended in air

place_name: New England Trail at Robinson State Park
review_text: Beautiful trail  with plenty of challenge...the reward is the view from atop Provin Mtn. Are you brave enough to ascend the fire tower?!

place_name: New England Trail at Robinson State Park
review_text: Fabulous hiking through the wilds of Central and Western Massachusetts, much of it along high ridges with spectacular valley views. The Berkshire AMC chapter even has a free ride service to avoid the three-mile road walk at the Westfield River, fordable only during low-water months.

place_name: New England Trail at Robinson State Park
review_text: Decent amount of trails. Nice river views

place_name: New England Trail at Robinson State Park
review_text: Nice quiet trails love it

place_name: New England Trail at Robinson State Park
review_text: Beautiful area for a hike.

place_name: New England Trail at Robinson State Park
review_text: Good riding

They are just a snooty clique of the towns rich. No real idea what art is. Theres so much talent in town but theyd rather spend money to bring in outsiders for displays and sales. Last time they rejected a local who made art from recycled trash into beautiful ships and airplanes, they put in the window the next day birdhouses made from old license plates! THATS your " art" expert community , westfield. I hate this town!
WOW is an essential, non-profit entity in Westfield. MusicFest, PumpkinFest, Lantern Light Parade, House Tour, Tree Jubilee - these are all events brought to Westfield by Westfield on Weekends.
The community events WOW puts on are amazing. Great for families.
Great family activities
Change it out online!!
Talented artists

Full disclosure: I am a member and volunteer as a Range Safety Officer. That being said, I have been a member of several shooting ranges over the years. But none of them had the number of versatile well kept ranges, friendly staff and members and focus on safety like this one. Our "high power" range offers several distances up to 400 yards. Our indoor-outdoor range lets you shoot from a building with fans when it's hot and a furnace when it's chilly, even lights to illuminate your targets when it's dark. Even if it's rainy or drizzly you stay dry as you turn a wheel to move your targets out and back in.We have over 2,200 members (as of June 2024); yet  you came come and find it uncrowded due to the number of ranges. Just like the gym, members never all show up at the same time. We also offer classes leading to a License to Carry permit which is needed if you want to shoot pistols. An FID card allows you to shoot rifles. If you have neither of these you can still shoot Black Powder and Archery. A "free Spouse" membership is offered and supervised children can have a ball at the fishing pond. Stop by and check it out.

Very nice clean place. Multiple ranges. There riffle range goes out to 300 yards. They have a skeet range, Archery course. There's a small fishing pond you can teach kids how to fish. You can shoot your pistol, shotgun, rifle, and bow all on the same place. The membership cost is a very fair price I love it here.

Great club for the entire family.  You have a fishing pond, archery range, pistol/handgun and 22 Rim Fire ranges, Trap/Skeet, Black Powder range, and Shotgun range.  What more could an outdoor sportsman want.  The Range Officers are all awesome.  If you follow the range rules you have no problem.  The range rules are for every members safety.  All I can say I have been a member since 1975 and have seen many improvements over many years and would expect more to be implemented.  Great sportsman club for the individual and family.

Great local range, staff has always been courteous. Never been bothered while shooting and if following the rules they should have no reason to approach you. My only complaint is if you pay for a year you should get a year but I guess if you have no way of keeping track of this then it's the members responsibility. If you truly want your money's worth just make sure you sign up on October 1st.

Edited: Updating my review since I was assisted by staff and all my concerns were addressed.

Its still weird that the membership is not pro rated, but in retrospec its still cheaper than other range memberships in the area by far with alot more to offer.

My only other gripe is that guests even with LTC are not allowed to join you to shoot, they must become a member. But again, this works both ways are a plus so you don't have random non members increasing risk of an incident.

Staff have been friendly since I've attended and any issues of unfairness or "making up rules as they go" can be brought to other staff or the owner and are usually worked out.
response_from_owner_text:
Hi Mr Doe,
You are not buying anything but paying dues as a member of a club. Yearly dues are what they are, regardless of when the member joins. Obviously we are not a good fit for each other. We suggest you check out Hot Brass, maybe their pricing structure will suit you better.

review_text: This is a great club for hunters, shooters, archers and fisherman. The club officers and range officers are committed to safety for all members. Ranges accommodate all disciplines of shooting and there are a lot events for anyone looking for something new and challenging.

Very great instructors! Personally like each one of them. They were very kind and made sure to answer our questions so that we understand gun safety and how to handle a gun. Can't wait to get my LTC! Definitely hope to become a member!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the kind words!

review_text:
To answer some of these issues. WSC have new directors. If someone is rude to you, contact the President asap. We have a membership of over 1400 people. We want everyone to enjoy their time at WSC.
If you wish to bring someone to the range for a tour, there is a range officer there and after signing a waiver, the range officer will gladly give you a tour. Guns are involved here, thus the liability is high. Insurance and city rules and state law require you to sign a waiver.
There are state and federal laws, read them. No person under the age of 21 can handle a firearm in the state of Massachusetts. So no you cannot bring someone to shoot underage, Long guns such as rifles and shotguns may be shot by a person over age 12 under the direction of an instructor or the childs parents. They must have a waiver signed by the parent, and possess a state mandated FID card at the appropriate age. that's the law. if other ranges allow otherwise, I would report them immediately.
there was an incident with a child several years ago due to a irresponsible parent and event sponsor. Sure we would love to introduce kids the world of firearms, but it has to be responsible and under the laws of the state. again if the child is under 12 and is shooting, it is illegal here.
IF YOUR LTC is expired, and you do not have a current one in hand, you now illegally possess a firearm no matter if you own it or not, this is a state law, read it. It does not matter if you reapplied, until you have it in hand, you will go to jail if caught with a firearm, PERIOD. If you wish to join another range, with a expired permit, even if the other one is on the way, you open up the range to millions in liability, and you jail time where you will never see your permit again ever, then go ahead. WSC will not allow you to join with out producing a valid LTC or FID. you may get a membership to use the other facilities and when you get your permit you can get full use of the ranges.
Hope this clears up the complaints, if you  have a problem at WSC, please contact the President, instead of complaining here, we will address any issues you have. Research the laws before placing blame on WSC. Once a accident happens at another range, they will start following the laws. The three closest ranges in the area aside of WSC allow members to break state and federal laws all day long, I have seen it for myself. Our rules follow all laws, and protect you and everyone on WSC property.

I am so happy I joined this facility, it's the happiest place with the friendliest people! It's made working out so much more enjoyable. The staff here are amazing and knowledgeable. The classes they offer are both professional and challenging, while also providing great social interaction. It's just a wonderful and fun YMCA. Amazing

Very rude people working over there I speak manager couple times she told me help me. I have autism kids. He's like the swimming and I go all the time over there all the time these people bother me bother them my autism kids make me racism this is not good my kids no,more like swimming  people forget the respect

I was a Paid Member between 2011 to 2023 & was Very Sad to have to change to Fitness First because it's On My way to work.
Westfield YMCA Gives You the "Most Bang for your Buck $$$ !!!" & It's amazing what they have available to You inside that Historical building !!!
A Lot of Fitness Facilities all wrapped in one !!!
I love this Y! The staff are friendly and the pool and gym are never crowded and always clean!
Bad customer service When the trainer give you an appointment and I come on time, they don't show up
I love going here I just wish they opened earlier since my work day starts pretty early.

Pretty quick to give up on my child who was trying to transition into preschool. Also, lack of communication when starting preschool. They don't tell you what to bring or who your kids "teacher" is going to be.
It is off full they said that Tuesday the YMCA is open and when I went there it was closed.

Another INCREDIBLE program put on by Roots. I am so deeply grateful for, and impressed with, how smoothly this camp ran. The communication was impeccable, my daughter was happy, and we did not get a single report of negative behavior about her all summer because the staff truly loved and worked with my child. Thank you ROOTS!
My kiddo loves going to the Roots camp. The counsellors are great with kids and helped my shy kid feel welcome. she made some great memories and new friends. we will definitely be going back.

The best summer ever
First experience using Roots Summer program and will not be the last. It was the  richest experience one could ever hope for. Staff was amazing, to say the least and communication was top notch.

This is one of the best vacation experiences our grandson has ever had! Well organized, well paced and FUN throughout the day. He looked forward to each and every day, and we were all sorry to have it end. Sign your child up. You won't be sorry.

If you're looking for a great summer camp or school vacation camp, you've found it!!!!
Coach Cody and all the staff are amazing, kind, caring and fun(so I'm told)!!!! We will definitely continue to use Roots Camp for as long as we can!
Parent Bonus: your kid(s) are tired when they come home!!!!!
Staff were enthusiastic, made connections with my camper, and engaged kiddos in fun activities.  Camp was great for my kiddo!
We love Roots camp!  Lots of great activities.
Thank you Conner had a great time .See you next year
What a wonderful library and staff ! So very welcoming and helpful. I had the pleasure of working in a study room, and it was so comfortable.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the kind review! We are glad you had a great visit!  For anyone in need of a quiet space, our study room can also be scheduled ahead of time by calling 413-568-7833 ext 2.

review_text:
Beautiful piece of westfield history, I definitely recommend looking into the history if the building! Its very interesting.
A very lovely and quiet library.

If you haven't been to the Westfield Athenaeum, you are missing out.  The programs and available items to check out is crazy good! Did you know you can check out an air fryer? I did! The staff here are kind , pleasant and always happy to assist with even the smallest request. Art shows, historical displays, and so much more.   We are so lucky to have this institution at our finger tips.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the 5 stars Michael!

review_text: The children's librarians are a hit or miss- half don't even say hello or acknowledge us when we walk in. Then they act like we are interrupting them when checking out books. So very weird. When I was a child all the librarians were super friendly and helpful
response_from_owner_text: Hi Sarah, we always want our patrons to feel welcome and we are so sorry you had this experience.  The Athenaeum strives to provide interesting programming, quality materials and a fun environment to our littlest patrons. Thank you for your feedback, and we will take a close look at how we can improve in this area.

review_text: I enjoy coming here with my kids... they have a lot of planned activities for kids (in the Boys and Girls Library part) and summer reading program. The building is beautiful (1800's) and includes an area to exhibit art. They do have a museum as well but I am not sure it has been open due to the pandemic. Worth seeing all the same. Helpful staff and  central location. Parking is on street as well as a parking lot (accessed from Court street - which has a ramp/wheelchair accessible entrance).
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the positive review! The Reed Room recently reopened with new history exhibits that are available to view anytime the library is open.

review_text: I feel blessed to live in a city with a wonderful library. The atheneum offers an array of services, programming, and a wide selection of items to borrow. In addition, the staff are friendly, efficient, and resourceful.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks so much! We're glad to hear you've been enjoying the library.

review_text: My son had a very serious accident in July so I am fully homeschooling him this year. We went to the library looking for 12th grade curriculum and Theresa was so helpful. Not only did she look up books for him, she took it upon herself to look up online resources and even sent an email after we left with more information. Now my son has plenty of resources to choose from for his senior year! Thank you so much for making a rough patch in our lives, easier.
Great place for books DVDs they have a good children's section too lots of toys for the kids to play with
response_from_owner_text: Thank you, Frank! Our staff appreciates your kind words!

review_text: How nice it is when just in a residential area there is a small oasis of peace, tranquility and beauty, where you can sit on a bench after a working day and listen to birdsong.  Walk among the blossoming daffodils.  It's great that someone once donated land, and someone now looks after it.  And there is where to run, walk and just sit !!!

Little gem of a garden with an interesting story. Volunteer maintained, but done well. Some common varieties, and some we had to research. Our visit happened to coincide with a 3rd grade school visit - charming!
Next door, part of the same 10 acre park, there stands a unique evergreen tree (see photo) looks a bit like a young Sequoia. Dated 1934. I could find no other info, but will do some research .

"If a man had a million dollars to build a memorial, he could not have achieved what the people of Westfield accomplish in creating the grandmother's garden"
(Albert Steigar)
Such a lovely place! It is truly a gem, gorgeous place run by volunteers.
So beautiful, just absolutely gorgeous. Such a hidden gem!
Absolutely beautiful. Came here foe my wedding and the gardens were in immaculate order. We Absolutely loved it and it made the day that much better

Grandmother's Garden is stunning. The beautiful variety of flowers are in bloom all spring, summer & and fall, and the grounds are very well maintained! It was very peaceful & calm. Its  like my own  hidden little "secret garden." What a gem.
I went to a friend's wedding & it was beautiful there
My son Jacob had an amazing time the last two weeks! He came home exhausted but happy and excited every morning to go to Kamp! Thank you to everyone there especially Tyler-Jacobs bff!

My boys had an amazing time at the summer program.   The staff were great with them and their ABA techs.  The company that habdled the transportation was incredible.   My only concern happened on a day with inclement weather...the program released early, but they didn't call to let parents know.
Nice facility, staff are kind and compassionate, many activities available for the kiddos
My daughter goes here every year and it is amazing for her and other special needs kids! Staff is wonderful!
A really great place for kids to hangout and try socializing with others, I went here as a kid and loved it a lot!
I have had nothing to do with this camp in my entire life. Why am I writing this? Seriously...
Camp for kids with special needs...
Best camp,ever
Nan runs a quality, social distant, and very safe group. Plenty of courts, lights at night, and great system of play using winners and "2nd place" system for grouping players.

Stopped there a few weeks ago passing thru the area.
Was welcomed and enjoyed the games.
Would like to return.
Thanks,
Bob
Best courts anywhere in the area.  How could anyone give it less than 5 stars?
I'm a beginner and I didn't feel intimidated, very nice group of new friends.
Best place to play.
Didn't realize what it was, but I thought it was cool to watch
Great people,  great courts, great activity, great sportsmanship,  beneficial and enjoyable!!!!!
My nieces have a BLAST at Roots they are involved in so much. Great place to keep your kids active in a healthy environment.
I play Non Peak Hours $10 soccer because lifting is boring and I need to run around former d1 baseball player. Love it! 10am-2pm weekdays youre usually good.
Great facility. Indoor fields and batting cages. Outside has fake turf and is great for soccer. Multiple fields.

place_name: Friends of the Westfield Senior Center
review_text: Nice new building friendly staff good all around experience

place_name: Friends of the Westfield Senior Center
review_text: Great people and atmosphere

place_name: Friends of the Westfield Senior Center

review_text: My favorite brewery in MA, a lot of people get really excited with one in specific, but I will talk about beer quality and no popularity, this guys brew one of my favorite Mexican inspired beers, a Pinneapple Jalapeno, as shows on the images they're really colorful, for a radpberry-banana, a blueberry-guava, strawberry-passionfruut and a regular NEIPA... again I gave the title of my favorite beer and brewery of the state based on the quality of the beer, and always visit the brewery is a great experience, if you see the smoke truck without hesitation try the food 100% recommended, I do recommend this brewery 100%!
Amazing weird beers you'd never expect!!! Traditionally beers plus an amazing selection of off camber beers  plus food outside. Perfect!!!!! Def a favorite wmass brewery. And a great staff!!!! Cheers

One of the things that makes Tin Bridge Brewery so compelling is that it seems so underwhelming at first glance. The ambiance and charm isn't immediately apparent until you sit at the tables and take in the rustic feel. Honestly, it's like a pop-up brewery-and every great brewery needs an unassuming place to start. Tucked behind a tiny strip mall, this place is worth a stop. The beers are creative, unique, and delicious. The New England IPAs don't simply rehash old formulas of just a citrus and haze feel, they add new twists that seem to work. In particular, the peanut butter porter is really quite good. We traveled over 75 minutes to get there and would definitely go there again.
response_from_owner_text: Thanks for visiting. We're glad you enjoyed!

review_text: Great brewery with regular special releases. Bar staff is attentive and waits for orders are quick even when it's busy. There are usually food trucks in the back area, although there is no outside area to stand with beer. There are also some arcade games, shuffle board, and even some traditional board games. The beer is top quality and they offer take home can growlers.

This place was great! The beers have crazy fun flavors and taste great. I'm not really a beer person, and from the 10 flight I liked 5 of them. So if you are not crazy into beers, this is a great place to try. The "Bubblezz" (don't know if I spelled it right) was a great choice if you don't like beer at all. The atmosphere was chill, and the food truck food was great too.
response_from_owner_text: We are so happy that you had a great experience. Thanks!

review_text:
I think they have the best IPAs and NE pale ale around... And their white chocolate peanut butter stout was actually fabulous? I wasn't a fan of the fruit beers but that is personal taste.

Not knocking them for the Mexican food truck (bc that's not their business) but that was very meh / not worth the price at all... 13 bucks for a very bland chicken quesadilla and 11 bucks for doritos with cold pumped nacho cheese on top... bleh.

The search continues for REALLY good food at a brewery in the area.... but if we're just talking beer, this place is top notch!

It was quite crowded on the day we visited, but tables kept turning over and we finally got one that was warmer and more socially distanced.
The beers are all very interesting!  While the really fruity ones aren't my normal go-to styles, it was interesting to try them.  Note that there are two sizes of flights.  The larger one has ten beers in it!
Parking is a little confusing.  Go around back or park on the side.  If you park in the lot towards Rt 20, you'll have to walk all the way around.

A brewery that tries. Good customer service, small space, and subpar beers equals a below average afternoon or evening. Tucked away awkwardly behind a strip mall, it'll take some beers with distinctive flavor to help them grow. Decent spot in a pinch, but definitely not a draw.
Beautiful views of Westfield Massachusetts  one thing I have to warn you , check for ticks on your body after, I got one and let me tell you, not something I want to relive again
The section I did was clean, easy to follow, and beautiful. Goes past an old quarry with beautiful views.
How can you not rate the great outdoors a "5"? This trail brings you to spectacular views on Provin Mountain.Wear sturdy shoes, bring a snack or lunch, water and your camera!
Great views, neat quarry and relatively easy hike.
Beautiful local trail with spectacular views of Southwick and the Berkshires
A bit of trash around, and I turned around at the river rather than fording it.
We had a great time hiking a little ways up the trail to swim and jump in off a rock. The water was super refreshing. Parking is quite limited so have a backup plan.
A beautiful gorge that is very easy to access. I definitely did not explore the whole area but what I saw was very beautiful. I definitely recommend visiting.

Growing up, this was the best teenager drinking spot. Apparently, it still is.

Time has warn down the trail and made it difficult to hike. Or maybe I am just older.

Still it is a wonderful place to sit,  relax, and listen to the calming sounds of a beautiful woodland stream

I loved this place. Very nice scenery for relaxing or photos. Nice swimming spot.
This place is beautiful and clean the way God intended it so 
Please don't leave trash lying around. The world isn't your trash bin. You know who you are.

Absolutely beautiful but unfortunately it's full of broken glass. Every single person in my party of 6 cut their feet either in the water or on the bank. I highly recommend wearing water shoes or anything but bare feet.

Difficult for me in my 50's. Big boulders to go up and down, and I have short legs. Some one sadly is not picking up after themselves. Enjoyed the quiet here by the river and there is swimming areas that are deep.

A nice nature spot that is overrun with broken pieces of glass and other trash. Always someone else there. Water is fairly shallow. The greenery is nice. Hike is treacherous. Not handicap accessible. Proximal to downtown Southwick. Small parking lot the has some broken glass, be mindful and be prepared to visit again another time if its too crowded and the lots full. Try ans bring a trash bag when you visit, to carry out your own waste (obviously) but also to carry out the ample trash already there. Graffiti on rocks, skillfull artists. Worth a visit, or a few, so long as you help preserve the integrity for future generations to come!

I love this place to death. One of the most beautiful and magical places in the area. It could be a little cleaner, but overall it's incredible. Go there for a swim, a short walk, a hike up the creek bed, just to relax or to fish.

Beautiful park! Lots of dog walkers, kids and bikes. There is the main trail and little just off trails all over. We have seen a momma black bear and her cubs here a few times.
There are no trash cans - so it's pack in and out. The gate closes at 4pm sharp, and it is $10 to get in (in season).  There are many different little lots to park around the park perimeter.
A wonderful place for a walk. It's a shame that dog walkers don't clean up after themselves, or they use a bag, and leave the bags all over the place.

Mid-May is here, and the bugs are starting to become active. Ticks, too. Lots of individual cyclists and groups are riding the trails. Monday evenings are especially busy! Make sure to check yourself & your 4-legged friends for ticks as you exit the park.

Went here for the open house and Canoe cruise. It was nice. I know this place can get crowded during the summer. Some play the music a little too loud. It was not too crowded the day I went. It is not free, $8 and over $30 if you are not from MA.

Great park with plenty of trails and spots for Activities. There is a nice network of trails for hiking and some biking paths as well. You could also just walk or run on the road. It is pet friendly and many people walk their dog here. I believe you can also fish and swim here.The only down side I see if they tend to close the gates a bit early. Many people just park on the street outside the gate however, which doesn't appear to be a big problem.

The hike is really beautiful but coming here for the first time it was confusing as there are no signs to direct you or maps.  There is a main road which you walk on but you hesitate to veer off the road in fear of getting lost.  Once we did we realized each trail looped around back to the main road.  There were beautiful waterfalls off the trails and really pretty scenery; just a suggestion to add more signs and it would make it perfect for those coming for the first time!  Would have hated missing all the park had to offer!
Nice park. Picnic areas with grills and tables. Rest room were clean. Lots of dogs with owners. Small beach area. Few long trails. No real views though.... but relaxing.

Nice clean park area, good winding trails through the woods, only hit a couple miles of them, but they were pretty clearly marked, it'd be hard to get lost though due to the fact that you're basically following the stream or the river on most of them.. lol but overall a nice spot! And if your pup likes the water there's plenty of spots for them to dunk in

They explained water safety, floating, breathing, and stroke techniques in different ways so my kid could understand what they were saying. She learned three times as much in one 30 minute evaluation/lesson in this 1:1 setting than she did in 10 classes at Goldfish Swim School. WEU provides a much greater value and service and I'm so glad we switched.

Got certified at the wilderness experience with Scott Cook in 2005. Had a excellent time did a lot of traveling and a lot of diving. Now retired living in Florida took a refresher course and back into diving the keys and warm water. Miss diving for the lobsters and scallops but don't miss the cold water and dry suit and lots of lead LOL. Being retired leaves much more time for diving and a new chapter in fun.
Thanks
Scott M.

The WEU summer camp is not worth it. They don't encourage kids to try new things, and they run the place like a reform school. There's lots of bored downtime(specifically on rock climbing day), they treat the older campers the same as the littles -  no running, no sarcasm, no fun. So disappointed.
Absolutely the people to book your next adventure with!!!!
Beautiful view, lots of varied trails, well-maintained, nice cabins and tent sites, picnic tables. Has what you want and need!

1. Picture right before the flurries got to Noble View

2. Nice upgrade with the generator. Definitely added in the last couple months

Many well-maintained trails for hikers of all levels. The pitcher trail leads to a series of beautiful waterfalls. The upper part of the venue offers great views of the Pioneer Valley; Be sure to bring binoculars! The Appalachian Mountain Club (AMC) really does a great job with this site.

sadly I missed the waterfall and hike i wanted to do since when you pull into the parking lot it doesn't really tell you thats the trail. I did hike the yellow noble one and thats pretty steep and some tough hills with a switch back for the small loop. but a view and you can see the cabin huts. i will have to go back when its not so hot for that waterfall and those trails

Great place to take the family to see the absolutely gorgeous Pitcher Falls located among the trails, that are fairly kid friendly throughout most of the trail system!!
* Pitcher Falls consists of 3 different categories of waterfall classification. Listed below is the order of which falls you come up to first if you enter from the parking lot up the road, right before the old farmhouse you see coming up the road when the gates are open after rainy season (Spring - usally after April, and sometime in early May they open regularly to avoid the roads being washed out.)
>> Upper Section * Slides
- *Don't Slide Down*

>> Middle Section * Cascades
- First waterpool, and look across the water from shoreline level to the base of a tree.. you'll notice a little "Fairy Box" built into it, please don't disturb it. Thank you!

>> Lower Section * Punchbowl
- Largest Waterfall and deepest pool of water among Pitcher Falls. Please no cliff jumping, it is not safe for anyone really.. even if it may look like it in certain spots. Just enjoy the waterfall & the wonderful photo opportunity & standing spots for various angles, and be careful & take all trash out.
Thank you very much for reading & hope you love Pitcher Falls as much as last person.

Beautiful view, well marked and easy to follow trails. Great place to get out in the woods and spend the day hiking. Trail map is accessible on your phone and seems very accurate. Do not expect amenities just the great outdoors!

Hiked here twice in the last 2 weeks. Nice area and interesting terrain with streams, small waterfalls, ravines, varied vegetation. Very lightly traveled during the week.
The trails are mostly fairly easy and not technical, albeit in a few places on the Border Trail steep.
Near the entrance, trails are well maintained with new blazes and good marking plaques. However, further South on the (yellow) Border Trail and the (red) Pitcher Brook Trail it appears that sections of the trails are being rerouted. The result is that the old sections are closed and/or hard to find (faded blazes, overgrown trail) while the new sections do not yet exist and/or are hard to find. Not a disaster but you have to be generally aware of where you are on the trail - and bring a map!

Stayed Memorial Day weekend. It is a volunteer AMC site, so no staff on site. Hut was clean, nice kitchen but no sink, restroom/shower/cleaning building were also very clean. Trails leading offsite were very wide and easy. Walked to two different falls where kids were able to swim and enjoy. Would return

Amazing food, along with great beer and staff, was very friendly and welcoming!!! They have outdoor seating and a downstairs for large groups.  Beautiful brewery and terrific setup!! Well worth the drive!! We loved the barbecue, and the fish and chips were a great hit!!! A must try
Clean, spacious, positive modern vibes, refreshing music. I had the cherry beer which was sour with a hint of chocolate. So good! Westfield needs a spot like this.

Excellent brewery and great atmosphere!  Beer selection is complete with offerings on just about every category.  Everything I have had has been fantastic.  Their food pairs well with their beers.  Great local bands/,musicians as well!

Fantastic location and very spacious inside.  Had great service and the beer selection was great. Had 2 flights and we enjoyed every beer we tried. So much so, we decided to take 3 four packs home with us. The food was also good and would highly recommend this brewery. The pretzel there is a delicious treat to have with beer .  They also have outdoor seating now which is wonderful to be honest

Great awakening is slowly becoming a staple to Westfield. They have phenomenal pub food with a wide variety of different options. The beer is always good IF you know what you like. Their light beers, in my opinion, have always hit spot on. They do trivia once a month, always have live music on the weekends. A great place and they are such a staple now compared to the big adventures which use to be there.

I believe Great Awakening has earned the right to be called the best spot for beer and a bite in Westfield. Beer selection and quality is simply unmatched! I love being able to get flights and try out their rotation of beers while also coming back for more of some of their mainstays (like Sicle!) And although the food menu is a bit limited, everything on it that I've tried tastes amazing. Also, such a cool location and atmosphere. Staff is so attentive and friendly. This place has it figured out!!
A lovely spot, equally good with a group or a small, intimate couples date.   Lot's of space to spread out.   Both beer and food choices are top notch.
Great experience! Both the beer and food were awesome! The owners did a great job putting it all together. I am sure they are going to have great success!
I've been coming here since a child and I can enjoy it with family and my kids are excited every time we go. Enjoy
Great place for a hike or picinic!! Good views also..

Would give it a 5, because this place was amazing. However, the staff working never informed several parties, as well as mine, what time the park closed. 5 or 6 cars were trapped in the parking lot with no staff around to remove the padlocks from the gate. We were all pretty ticked off, but we managed to move the boulders around out front, to make room for the cars to finally get out. Was quite the venture for sure...

The Swimming here is great and they have little camp sites with grills that can be used. Parking isn't always available though. This changes year to year and depends on if they staff the park. I would NOT park along the side of the road here (outside the gate). Police are very quick to have you towed and it's also a pretty tight road with very little shoulder. Hopefully they open it up to the public in the future :)

Absolutely beautiful! The park is open everyday from 10a until 5p. A nice place 2 walk & enjoy nature's beauty, great place 2 bring ur kids 2 get wet, u can also soak in the sun if u like. U could bring a cooler with ur favorite goodies, bcuz picnic tables r set-up 2 sit down 2 eat & even hear the music of the water running over the rocks, plenty of portable bathrooms r available as well. We had a great time, not a lot of people were here, but the ones that we're here did leave enough distance from each other. Come on down, bcuz I know u will love it 2, remember masks must b worn.

Unfortunately the park is over run with people coming from the surrounding cities..not watching their kids....there were young children going through our things because they wanted to play with my kids toys...right on the beach while the parents were up in the woods...people leaving their garbage everywhere. It's a shame..would be a beautiful spot if people could just pick up after themselves and take care of their children.
Such a  laid-back place to go
Pretty Deep from all the Rain Last week and before Strong Currents... so far the Rain still comes and Goes

Tekoa Country Club is a wonderful venue for our annual fundraising St. Mary's High School Green & Gold Gala! Destiny and the entire staff are friendly, accommodating and flexible. They hosted our event the past two years and we already booked for next year - cannot wait!

Destiny & the entire staff at Tekoa Country Club were absolutely phenomenal for our wedding. Destiny is not only very professional but she is incredibly kind and superb at her job. Throughout the entire process she handled everything with ease and treated us like we were the only wedding happening. Our big day was even better than we could have imagined. The decor, food, and atmosphere was perfect. If you choose to book your wedding with TCC you will not regret it!

We had the pleasure of working with Destiny at Tekoa to plan a graduation party.  We were looking for a venue that could offer flexibility, creative ideas, an indoor space with an outdoor option (a deck), convenience, ease in planning, a fun venue for guests of all ages, and a great location.  We found all of that and more with Tekoa!  Destiny guided us along the way based on our questions and general ideas about the party, offering really helpful suggestions along the way based on her experience and expertise to build up to a fantastic, well organized, much enjoyed party!  It was such a relief to be able to count on Tekoa to decorate the room with our party decorations, pictures, etc., and to be able to use the items Tekoa had as well (including tablecloths, napkins, a photo backdrop, candle centerpieces, a gift card holder, etc.).   And it was great not to have to buy/prep/store/serve the food on our own - Tekoa took care of it all!  It was great to have the deck to use as some guests preferred outdoor space which also had seating.  Throughout the entire process, Destiny was prompt in answering any questions that came up; during the party Destiny and her staff were wonderful, always making sure that everything was going well.  I wholeheartedly recommend Tekoa for any of your party/banquet needs!

We celebrated our annual awards banquet with 340 members. Everyone at Tekoa was so easy and fun to work with.  Destiny and her AMAZING crew made the night go flawless. The planning prior was easy with Destiny's expertise. She was very helpful with any of our questions. We ended up using both of the bars for our event and it worked perfect. Lines moved great! Also the FOOD...everyone gave 5 stars!!!

Let me just say thank you to Destiny  she was an amazing coordinator she made sure my wedding day was special she made sure everything was organized Tekoa staff was amazing!!! I  recommend  them 100 percent

Great place with beautiful views! We rented a banquet hall for a 60th birthday and it was great experience! Hall is beautiful! They set up everything the way you want it.  Food was delicious! Beautiful views outside to chill and take pictures.

Jennifer and her staff did an amazing job. They decorated with such passion. They made the day so special for myself and my husband.  The food was amazing. Jeff the chef and his team did such an amazing job. Tekoa is a wonderful place to have your wedding and reception. Jennifer paid attention to all details we described to her. She is very attentive and always responsive to my calls and emails.  She included my husband and I in all the planning. She walked us step by step through the process.

Hot day and the course is great condition... greens are quite fast making it a little more challenging... some of the wholes have extended blue tee boxes (set back) adding a little bit more of a challenge. Very relaxed atmosphere... I recommend it.

The Westfield yoga Center really lives up to its name.
Sally and Tom are such inviting and warm people that it's easy to want to come back very week! Sally teaches yoga in a beautiful way that even in the beginner level you can feel the sense of connection/unity of mind, body, and "time bound consciousness" as she says. They aren't just teaching yoga, they are living the yogic lifestyle and inviting people in the community to share in it.
The long and short of it is I highly recommend.

Sally is an excellent yoga instructor, she has a great sense of humor and makes the difficulty of some poses easier as she offers direction on how to alter it according to what type of pain or discomfort you are feeling. I have been to many different styles of yoga and some can feel like people are in competition with each other, but Sally fosters a sense of inclusivity and integrity.
She also gives us broader info about the Yogic lifestyle and how to alter your thoughts and be happier and more in tune with yourself. They offer all kinds of yoga classes, and add-on classes- special events like Yoga Nidra on thursdays, her and Tom are great, and her craniosacral sessions are very healing too! They are top of my list and many others!!

Westfield Yoga Center is a wonderful!  The owners Sally and Tom are so kind and caring!  Sally's yoga Nidra is amazing and full of her loving, peaceful energy!
Basic yoga on Tuesday evenings by Jackie Furnaro is so great and anyone can do it!  Jackie incorporates not just yoga asanas, but pulls in ideas for healing body, mind and spirit such as making affirmations, journaling and meditation!
I recommend any who wants to give yoga a try to attend one of Jackie's classes!
Westfield Yoga Center is the best! Each class and instructor are amazing!
Very relaxing and friendly atmosphere. Love going there!
Very peaceful and welcoming.
Excellent class
Wonderful!
Hello my name is sumitra darji i have to quarantine  if you don't mind can you call me back
The WHS Show Choir has a great time today! Thank you for the wonderful experience!

I can not recommend A Stables more. Their staff are friendly, knowledgeable and patient. They are generous with their time. The horses are wonderfully trained and beautiful. I took a couple for a photo shoot here and the staff made sure they got all the shots they possibly could want and the couple had a very fun day.
They are very supportive and flexible. I have had nothing but great interactions and experiences for both my 5 year old and 13 year old!

Woronoco Falls: A Hidden Gem in Western Massachusetts

Nestled in the small town of Russell, Massachusetts, Woronoco Falls offers a picturesque escape into nature. The waterfall cascades down a series of rocky ledges, creating a mesmerizing display of water and moss-covered stone.

What to expect:

Short Hike: The falls are accessible via a short, easy hike along a mostly flat trail, making it suitable for most visitors.
Picturesque Setting: The surrounding woodlands, especially vibrant during the fall foliage season, create a stunning backdrop for the waterfall.
Swimming Hole: A small pool at the base of the falls is popular for cooling off on warm days.
Tips:

Best after rain: The falls are most impressive after a recent rainfall.
Picnic Spot: Pack a lunch and enjoy a peaceful picnic by the water.
Footwear: Wear comfortable shoes suitable for a short walk in the woods.

Overall, Woronoco Falls is a lovely destination for a quick nature break and excellent if you're looking for a charming, lesser-known spot to explore in the area.

A fire earlier this summer destroyed part of one of the brick mill building, and for some time has effected/limited access to a few of the best swimming spots.  Wherever you plan to swim park at the designated parking area, with space for four or five vehicles, located across the bridge, at the end of Tekoa Avenue.
Parking anywhere else can result in being hit with a fifty dollar fine issued by Town of Russell police, who regularly patrol the area.

place_name: Team Link Westfield Brazilian Jiu Jitsu
review_text:
I have been a member of Team Link since 2016 on and off due to recovery from different kind of sports injuries or car accidents. I love BJJ and atmosphere in Team Link so I always come back to training whenever my body starts feeling  better. . There are several  " team link "gyms in other towns beside this fairly new one in Westfield. What  is nice about  having such a great big community is - I was able to train under many instructors  and get so much more experience . Some memberships allow  you to go to any team link gym regardless of the town.
Last year , I joined team link in Westfield for many reasons and I hope I can  encourage you to join as well. :)
First of all , as I mentioned before it is a new gym that just opened up in September 2023 - it is the biggest by size in the area and has new MATTS- the best quality ones (when you land you barely feel lol ), second - wonderful, knowledgeable instructors ( black and brown belts ) . Each of them is fantastic.
Third - as a woman,  I never feel as I need to worry about someone being too harsh with me . They are plenty of strong and mighty women there to begin with  haha and even if I end up to have a male partner - all of them are super nice and there is no bad blood between anyone. Everyone works as a team and helps each other in a nice friendly atmosphere. In fact - this is the best time to join if you are new to MMA or BJJJ since a lot of new members joined and  you can easily catch up with presented techniques if you come consistently. There are classes for kids too. You have so many sessions available -from evenings and mornings - which is  my fourth reason I joined. I love the morning Tuesdays and Thursdays sessions at 9:30 am ( thank you  to my great instructors Tom, Brian and Jovan for their patience,encouragement and attention to details and to all my friendly colleagues at team link  ).  I also come in the evenings when I can and everyone there is super nice too !
When you join and you are new to MMA - you won't be sparring right away until you learn the basics which provides everyone with additional safety and helps us all to decrease unnecessary injuries.
So , here we come to my fifth and last reason why I chose Team Link  - it provides safe and pleasant environment to train regardless of you age or gender . When you work with your partner you need to be honest about any injuries you might be recovering from and no one here will be trying to work against you but with you !!!! We are all here to WIN against our "own self " and become a better or best version of " you " .

When you ready to join ( or want to learn more )speak to Tom. He will do all the paperwork with you.
If it was not for him I probably would not have join again last year but he always  encourages me to do the best I can , even when my body does not always cooperate. No one here forces you to do ALL techniques and if for some reason you cannot perform it -you don't have to .
Thank you to Marco Alvan our head coach/instructor #1  from
Ludlow ( you have always been so kind to me ) and other instructors from Northampton that helped my growth so much  ( Gary and his wonderful  wife Jeileen) - and to many more that had been there for me since the beginning. Love you all !!!!!
Ps . This is officially the longest review I have ever written  haha

We saw turtles, fishy, some kind of water snake, and a giant turtle eating a baby turtle!!!! Awesome experience, kids loved it, unexpected landscape, beautiful. Loved that there were no dogs. Nice atmosphere among walkers.

Great place for flat ground hiking/Walking. I went with a small group and walked 4 1/2 miles along the trail. Saw lots of turtles, geese and ducks and also some fish and frogs. There is a large parking lot at the entrance and a couple of port-a-pots strategically placed on the trail. The area is well manicured and a wonderful place to take a walk, run, or bike. Very peaceful here. I heard that bugs can be a problem but none today.

Such a beautiful place to walk. Easy parking and nice flat routes so that you go at a leisurely pace if you like ...nice long routes that loop around. you could spend hours walking about taking in the beautiful nature! saw some lovely birds and brooks.

One of my favourite places  I love it.
Parking is free, there are a lot of ducks, squirrels, birds, turtles, fishes, etc. I also saw two beavers swimming.
Excellent place to walk, run, bicycle.
So peaceful, it has a lot of benches to sit all around the paths.
Be aware with snakes!, A lady told me she saw a Rattle-snake when I was there.

Great place for running.
Sunsets look beautiful. Love the lotus flowers.

Absolutely beautiful reservoir. Trails are mostly flat. There is wildlife including geese as well as other water are living creatures. There are many benches follow the trails and some interesting sites along the way. No dogs allowed as it is a reservoir

Very peaceful and quiet walking, with just the sound of the crunching gravel under foot and the nature around. Canadian Geese were around, and lots of droppings cover the pathways, so watch your step! You can also bring your bike for a nice bike ride.
Favorite spot to walk and relax!

Great venue for a good time in Westfield. Parking is easy (even if the lot is full, street parking is only 2mins away). Entry is quick and painless, concessions are fast and lines are short. Food cost is low and beer cost is about $5.00 for domestic and $6 for premium. Beer garden is a good idea however, you can get stuck as you can only walk to it between 1/2  innings. Reserving a seat is easy and the seats have tons of room for legs, knees and elbows. Seats and GA along the left field / first base side get shade first but every seat gives you a great view. It seems like sunflower seeds don't get cleaned up as well as they could be but, the seating area is relatively clean.

Staff is excellent, and restrooms are about the norm for a college game (not super clean but definitely fine to use)

Overall, a great place to go with kids and have a great time!

You will get a good night of baseball. It is well worth it. Only downside would be it is general admission. Would love to see them add more seats. Think if they put some work into it they may really take off.

Always a great place to catch a ball game.
Could be a high school game or the Westfield Starfires. Part of the collegiate League
Amazing game double header. Westfield Starfires are a great team. Real potential. Loved the stadium it's worth a look and a game.
Beautiful and historic ball park in Mt hometown. Definitely catch a game there if you can! Fun fact this is also where most Westfield teens have their high-school graduation!!!

The baseball field is very well maintained and I'm a fan of the renovated seating behind the diamond. Always a good experience watching a baseball game. Good selections to choose from at concessions and it won't really hurt your wallet. I only wish they would pay more attention to the football field as it needs a face-lift.

Overall it needs a clean up and some renovation but they did have a good concessions stand with good food and merchandise which was nice. Hopefully we see some renovations soon. Go Starfires!

review_text: If you or your child plays soccer, you can't beat this state of the art facility. Has 3 indoor fields, a raised indoor track, and will be opening food vendors. Great views of two fields from the mezzanine.

Incredible historic bridges that were part of the first railroad to cross mountains in the world! An engineering marvel and a beautiful hike of 2 miles each way to take it all in. A great way to share history with children- there are multiple kiosks along the way with facts and figures on this tremendous endeavor.

Nice hike with interesting history. It's an easy hike. There is about 600 feet of total elevation gain over the 5 mile hike. If you have limited mobility it would be tough due to uneven ground, sand and rocks on the path. The river and woods are pretty and the arches are a nice bonus. We enjoyed even in the rain.

Completed the Keystone arch bridges trail today. A very well marked and fairly easy trail of 2.5 miles to the end and then back. There are informative signs about the bridges and the railroad that once went over them. Although the bridges and the railroad cutouts are the draw here, the river is nice and the trail goes along the river for the most part. I think when there isn't a drought there are a couple small brooks and waterfalls that the trail crosses.

Awesome morning walk. Unfortunately, because fallen foliage is hiding the path, there aren't enough trail markers to be effective! Lots of new markers, but not enough, especially at turns... Great walk though.

I sometimes steer clear of out-and-back trails, but I'm glad we tried this one. The stone bridges towering over the river are very impressive, but even without the bridges, the river views are spectacular. This route gains a modest amount of elevation going out, as the path travels upriver. The trail is mostly easy walking, often wide enough for two people to walk comfortably side by side. Some sections are a bit muddy. In one section, the trail turns right, narrows and gains a bit of elevation before a footbridge crosses a cascading stream, then winds down to follow the river again. There are a few opportunities to venture off the main KAB trail (blazed with blue metal tags); these offshoots can provide the best views of the bridges. The bridge toward the end provides a great view downriver for a lunch break.
Awesome trail.  About 5 miles out and back.  Steep hikes to get to the base of the arches.   Cool swimming holes along the way as well. Dog friendly

This place is a real treat. I enjoyed the quiet nature of the trail and was really impressed with the bridges. I ended up encountering some train tracks and, due to fortuitous timing, I got to watch a train pass by. This place is definitely worth the drive.
